WEBVTT

00:01.318 --> 00:04.061
<i> THONY: Previously</i>
<i> on "The Cleaning Lady..."</i>

00:04.079 --> 00:06.488
I'm just a cleaning lady.
Let me clean it for you.

00:06.507 --> 00:08.674
Just let her do her job.
You might learn something.

00:08.751 --> 00:11.251
<i> THONY: You don't know how bad</i>
<i> it got before we came here.</i>

00:11.403 --> 00:14.071
We almost lost our home.
Our car got repossessed.

00:14.089 --> 00:15.072
Our friends
stopped talking to us.

00:15.074 --> 00:16.164
I think
you should go back home.

00:16.183 --> 00:18.684
No. I won't be separated
from my son again.

00:18.835 --> 00:20.001
I have to face Hayak.

00:20.079 --> 00:21.520
He's way too dangerous.

00:21.597 --> 00:24.172
<i> ARMAN:</i>
<i> He knows he didn't kill me.</i>

00:24.250 --> 00:25.507
THONY:
Wanna play a game?

00:25.526 --> 00:27.008
You're gonna pretend
Dara is your mommy.

00:27.028 --> 00:28.510
<i> And if we get separated,</i>

00:28.529 --> 00:30.345
<i> we're gonna have to race</i>
<i> to see who gets back first.</i>

00:30.439 --> 00:31.938
Can you step out
of the car, please?

00:32.015 --> 00:33.681
(dog barking)

00:33.759 --> 00:35.701
(whistle shrills)

00:35.852 --> 00:37.052
RUSSO:
Thony De La Rosa,

00:37.054 --> 00:38.495
you have the right
to remain silent.

00:45.862 --> 00:47.463
(thunder rumbles)

00:53.112 --> 00:56.722
(TV drones in background)

01:02.045 --> 01:04.897
<i> (tense music)</i>

01:04.973 --> 01:11.403
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:29.815 --> 01:32.591
(lightning cracking)

01:34.169 --> 01:38.822
<i> (intense, percussive music)</i>

01:38.841 --> 01:39.990
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:39.992 --> 01:41.975
(thunder cracks, rumbles)

01:53.096 --> 01:55.239
MARCO:
Thony!

01:59.178 --> 02:01.011
THONY:
Sit.

02:01.029 --> 02:02.454
Okay.

02:04.125 --> 02:06.291
MARCO:
Thony, Thony!

02:06.368 --> 02:07.868
What are you doing?
You're going without me?

02:07.944 --> 02:10.203
I have to take Luca now,
Marco.

02:10.280 --> 02:12.297
No, no. We wait
until my visa comes through.

02:12.299 --> 02:13.357
I can't wait.

02:13.450 --> 02:15.175
You know how hard it was
to find a donor.

02:15.210 --> 02:17.527
No, he's my son too.
We do this together!

02:17.529 --> 02:18.786
THONY:
No. Ah--no.

02:18.806 --> 02:20.139
Stop!

02:21.976 --> 02:24.868
MARCO:
Thony! Thony!

02:24.887 --> 02:26.562
(speaking Tagalog)

02:29.150 --> 02:30.891
MARCO:
Thony!

02:30.967 --> 02:32.693
Thony!

02:33.821 --> 02:36.213
Thony!

02:36.231 --> 02:37.731
UNIDENTIFIED VOICE:
<i> Thony.</i>

02:37.883 --> 02:40.141
Thony De La Rosa.

02:40.219 --> 02:43.370
Get up.
Let's go.

02:45.649 --> 02:47.815
<i> THONY: I don't know</i>
<i> what else you think I can do.</i>

02:47.835 --> 02:48.983
I told you everything.

02:49.077 --> 02:50.243
RUSSO: According
to Special Agent Miller,

02:50.396 --> 02:52.078
you've been working both sides,

02:52.231 --> 02:53.655
feeding us false information.

02:53.749 --> 02:57.325
If you need reminding,
that is obstruction of justice,

02:57.344 --> 02:59.511
lying to a federal agent,
aiding and abetting.

02:59.663 --> 03:00.921
GARRETT: Look,
I think she gets the point.

03:01.073 --> 03:02.181
It's prosecutable crimes.

03:02.349 --> 03:04.183
It could carry sentences
of two to five years each.

03:04.334 --> 03:06.334
-I need to get back to my son.
-RUSSO: I don't think

03:06.353 --> 03:08.520
you quite understand
what's happening here.

03:08.672 --> 03:11.339
We're not talking about
deportation anymore.

03:11.433 --> 03:14.768
If you don't help us
with this case now,

03:14.844 --> 03:16.528
you're going to jail.

03:16.721 --> 03:17.845
Don't look at him.

03:17.865 --> 03:20.014
If he can't make an arrest

03:20.034 --> 03:21.700
before the ATF seizes the guns,

03:21.777 --> 03:24.620
we are terminating Special
Agent Miller from the FBI.

03:26.098 --> 03:28.765
-Miller will take you home now.
-(sighs)

03:28.784 --> 03:30.116
Check in with your family,

03:30.269 --> 03:33.286
and then get back in contact
with Arman Morales.

03:33.439 --> 03:35.288
We know that
he hasn't moved the guns.

03:35.365 --> 03:37.274
So find out what's going on.

03:37.276 --> 03:39.793
And don't even think about
leaving the country.

03:39.945 --> 03:42.870
You will be arrested.

03:42.890 --> 03:44.556
If you don't fully comply,

03:44.633 --> 03:48.118
you will be locked up
for a very long time.

03:48.120 --> 03:50.804
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

03:50.880 --> 03:53.974
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:54.050 --> 03:56.884
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

03:56.962 --> 04:00.530
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:03.727 --> 04:06.078
(background chatter)

04:06.305 --> 04:09.665
(engine humming)

04:18.817 --> 04:21.593
<i> (tense music)</i>

04:21.745 --> 04:24.763
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:24.840 --> 04:26.265
(whistles)

04:45.435 --> 04:47.694
ARMAN: I got the message
you sent to my home.

04:47.846 --> 04:51.206
You didn't have to kill Carlos.
He had nothing to do with this.

04:53.276 --> 04:55.852
You could have told me
what you were really doing.

04:55.854 --> 04:57.111
You chose not to.

04:57.131 --> 04:59.947
You found a buyer.
You negotiated price.

05:00.025 --> 05:01.115
You betrayed me.

05:01.135 --> 05:03.543
When you gave that hotel
to Isabel and Ben,

05:03.620 --> 05:05.211
you betrayed me.

05:05.364 --> 05:07.472
All this talk
about us becoming partners.

05:07.624 --> 05:10.267
(laughing)

05:11.312 --> 05:14.054
Never enough. Always more.

05:14.206 --> 05:16.481
I came here to settle things
with you.

05:16.633 --> 05:20.043
You're in no position
to negotiate.

05:20.045 --> 05:22.562
You have nothing.
You are nothing.

05:22.714 --> 05:24.230
I would disagree.

05:24.307 --> 05:26.842
I still have the buyer.

05:26.844 --> 05:28.718
And he'll only deal with me.

05:28.737 --> 05:29.903
So here's my offer.

05:29.997 --> 05:32.647
I sell the guns,
and you take all the money.

05:32.666 --> 05:36.335
All I'm asking in return
is Nadia and I walk.

05:36.411 --> 05:40.413
That's $6 million
in exchange for our lives.

05:40.490 --> 05:44.584
And Nadia and I run the club
until the deal is closed.

05:44.661 --> 05:46.136
Then we're out.

05:52.019 --> 05:54.436
LUCA: I did not
like that game, Mommy.

05:56.023 --> 05:58.106
I know, peanut.

06:00.268 --> 06:05.605
We're never, ever gonna
be separated like that again.

06:05.757 --> 06:07.407
-Okay?
-Okay.

06:08.702 --> 06:11.761
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

06:11.780 --> 06:13.930
But Mommy's got to go to work.

06:13.949 --> 06:15.949
So you sleep now?

06:16.025 --> 06:17.501
-Okay.
-Yeah?

06:18.937 --> 06:20.103
I love you, peanut.

06:20.105 --> 06:22.464
I love you.

06:28.705 --> 06:30.222
FIONA: Just remember
what she went through.

06:30.298 --> 06:33.207
It worked.
Luca's going to be okay.

06:33.301 --> 06:34.893
Why can't you guys
just stay here?

06:35.044 --> 06:36.210
MARCO:
And live a life of a TNT?

06:36.288 --> 06:40.624
No. I want more for my son.

06:40.642 --> 06:41.650
Thony.

06:43.145 --> 06:45.795
Thony.
We need to talk, Thony.

06:45.814 --> 06:47.406
We will, just not now.

06:47.408 --> 06:49.649
I need to find post-op meds
for Luca.

06:49.801 --> 06:52.744
The hospital only gave us
enough to last for the week.

06:52.821 --> 06:54.079
Which is why
we should go home,

06:54.156 --> 06:55.972
where we can get Luca
what he needs.

06:55.974 --> 06:58.992
I told you,
I can't leave the country.

06:59.144 --> 07:00.335
They'll arrest me.

07:03.331 --> 07:05.072
I'll be back
before you go to work.

07:05.150 --> 07:06.716
No problem.

07:08.336 --> 07:10.262
Can you call Samentha
and find out the number

07:10.338 --> 07:11.746
of this guy
she buys insulin from?

07:11.765 --> 07:14.182
Sure. Good luck.

07:14.993 --> 07:16.342
Thanks.

07:16.495 --> 07:20.163
You had so many chances
to tell me about the FBI.

07:20.256 --> 07:22.165
And now it's too late.

07:22.258 --> 07:23.683
There was nothing
you could have done.

07:23.835 --> 07:25.110
That's not the point.

07:25.261 --> 07:26.686
You could have included me
in your life.

07:26.838 --> 07:29.172
Why don't you just give this
guy up and be done with it?

07:29.191 --> 07:31.841
Why are you protecting him
instead of us?

07:31.860 --> 07:35.845
<i> (tense music)</i>

07:35.847 --> 07:39.048
Luca is alive because of Arman.

07:39.050 --> 07:46.131
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:47.075 --> 07:50.260
(indistinct chatter)

07:54.216 --> 07:56.224
HOST:
Can I help you with anything?

08:01.540 --> 08:02.964
NADIA: Where do you think
you're going?

08:02.983 --> 08:05.542
Maybe Arman
forgot to tell you,

08:05.544 --> 08:08.570
but your services are no longer
needed here at the club.

08:10.065 --> 08:11.656
I just need to talk to him.

08:15.162 --> 08:17.737
Your little boy, he's okay?

08:17.814 --> 08:19.331
Yes.

08:21.335 --> 08:24.728
Then you already got what
you wanted from my husband.

08:24.821 --> 08:26.004
Now leave us alone.

08:27.399 --> 08:30.157
ARMAN: Hey, Thony.
Would you come on back, please?

08:30.235 --> 08:34.087
(both speaking Spanish)

08:34.239 --> 08:36.163
<i> Por favor ya.</i>

08:36.241 --> 08:39.333
<i> (tense music)</i>

08:39.353 --> 08:45.649
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:51.923 --> 08:53.365
How are you?

08:55.852 --> 08:57.927
I'm all right.

08:57.946 --> 08:59.454
And how's Luca?

09:00.965 --> 09:02.857
He's gonna be fine.

09:02.934 --> 09:04.251
(exhales)

09:06.696 --> 09:08.288
What about you?

09:08.440 --> 09:10.698
I was able to work
something out with Hayak

09:10.776 --> 09:13.218
to do the gun deal with him,

09:13.369 --> 09:15.870
but I'm gonna need your help
to get the Feds off my back.

09:15.947 --> 09:17.872
You can't do that.

09:17.949 --> 09:19.558
They know where the guns are.

09:19.560 --> 09:22.060
Both the FBI and the ATF
are watching the bar now.

09:22.211 --> 09:23.453
And how the hell
did they find that out?

09:23.471 --> 09:24.454
I don't know.

09:24.472 --> 09:25.972
But if you try
to move the guns,

09:26.124 --> 09:28.316
they'll arrest you.

09:30.404 --> 09:32.219
Thony, if I don't
close this deal

09:32.239 --> 09:34.072
and get Hayak his money,

09:34.223 --> 09:35.723
I mean, he'll finish me.

09:35.742 --> 09:40.136
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

09:40.138 --> 09:42.163
Maybe there's another way.

09:44.142 --> 09:48.311
What if I could help you
make a deal with the FBI?

09:48.330 --> 09:50.922
You could
help them arrest Hayak,

09:50.999 --> 09:53.166
and maybe they'll let you go.

09:53.242 --> 09:55.677
That's not gonna happen,
Thony.

09:57.246 --> 09:59.097
Then Hayak will kill you

09:59.174 --> 10:01.099
and the Feds will put me
in jail.

10:01.250 --> 10:03.250
Wait, what--what
do you mean?

10:03.270 --> 10:05.437
You have nothing
to do with this.

10:05.588 --> 10:07.397
(sighs)

10:10.185 --> 10:12.611
When you couldn't get me
out of Mexico,

10:12.762 --> 10:14.237
I had to call Garrett.

10:16.099 --> 10:17.841
He didn't have
the right paperwork,

10:17.934 --> 10:19.100
tried to smuggle me back,

10:19.177 --> 10:22.436
and we got caught
at the border.

10:22.514 --> 10:25.790
Arman, they know I've been
lying to them, okay?

10:25.867 --> 10:27.108
And now they're forcing me

10:27.185 --> 10:29.110
to help them set up
a sting operation.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.855
And set me up.

10:31.873 --> 10:34.040
Yes.

10:34.192 --> 10:36.117
But if we give them
Hayak instead--

10:36.194 --> 10:38.511
How am I supposed to work
with the FBI, Thony?

10:40.215 --> 10:43.516
Isn't that what you want?
To be free from him?

10:45.053 --> 10:47.187
Not that way.

10:47.981 --> 10:50.732
What other choice do we have?

10:55.547 --> 10:57.805
GARRETT:
No. That is not what we agreed.

10:57.899 --> 10:59.382
Arman is a criminal.

10:59.401 --> 11:01.159
He killed Knight.
He killed my last informant.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.218
He's not getting away
with that.

11:02.220 --> 11:05.388
Wait, who was your informant?

11:05.407 --> 11:06.572
Theo.

11:06.725 --> 11:10.226
(sighs) And I didn't do
enough to protect him.

11:10.228 --> 11:14.714
I am not gonna let Arman walk
after what he did to him.

11:15.901 --> 11:17.008
Arman didn't kill Theo.

11:17.160 --> 11:18.659
Whether he pulled the trigger

11:18.712 --> 11:21.012
or had of one of his boys
do it, it's all the same.

11:21.164 --> 11:23.515
No, it's not.

11:23.666 --> 11:26.518
Hayak's son killed Theo
and Arman tried to stop him.

11:26.594 --> 11:29.020
And it was over a fixed fight.
It had nothing to do

11:29.097 --> 11:30.355
-with him being an informant.
-All right, okay.

11:30.432 --> 11:32.506
Is that what Arman told you
to say?

11:32.526 --> 11:34.484
No, I saw it.

11:37.013 --> 11:39.513
Theo was a good man...

11:39.533 --> 11:43.034
and I had to clean his blood
off the floor to stay alive.

11:43.111 --> 11:45.929
That's what
I've had to deal with.

11:45.947 --> 11:47.430
And Arman saved my life
that night.

11:47.523 --> 11:50.417
So don't ask me to betray him.
I won't.

11:52.713 --> 11:54.028
Work with him.

11:54.105 --> 11:56.548
He can help you get Hayak.

11:56.699 --> 11:58.958
Come on, Thony.

11:59.035 --> 12:02.795
I mean, you really think that
he's gonna give up his boss?

12:02.948 --> 12:04.948
The reason
I got stuck in Mexico

12:04.950 --> 12:08.042
is because Hayak tried
to kill him.

12:08.061 --> 12:10.136
I really think he's gonna
make a deal with you.

12:10.288 --> 12:12.956
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

12:12.974 --> 12:15.734
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:26.321 --> 12:29.655
(music, singing in distance)

12:29.732 --> 12:33.918
♪ ♪

12:34.070 --> 12:35.161
(door chimes jangle)

12:35.238 --> 12:38.739
(indistinct chatter)

12:38.759 --> 12:45.430
♪ ♪

12:45.507 --> 12:48.415
All right,
if we're gonna do this,

12:48.493 --> 12:50.584
I need to be
the one calling the shots.

12:50.662 --> 12:54.347
I know too many people who got
burned doing deals like these.

12:54.499 --> 12:56.524
-(door chimes jangle)
-Yeah.

13:06.027 --> 13:09.537
Arman.
Thanks for meeting.

13:10.698 --> 13:11.748
That's all this is.

13:16.797 --> 13:18.463
Um, shall we sit?

13:22.618 --> 13:24.594
You can sit here.

13:37.317 --> 13:39.967
You cooperate with us,
we can work something out.

13:39.986 --> 13:43.137
Who said I'm cooperating?

13:43.214 --> 13:44.989
I'm here because of her.
That's all.

13:45.066 --> 13:48.159
As you know,
we've got eyes on the guns.

13:48.311 --> 13:52.163
Any movement of those weapons
will result in an arrest.

14:00.156 --> 14:02.257
It doesn't have to be you.

14:03.751 --> 14:05.218
Hmm.

14:11.242 --> 14:14.577
If we can't
figure it out together,

14:14.579 --> 14:16.229
we all lose.

14:25.031 --> 14:27.532
Arman, please.

14:33.948 --> 14:35.206
How would this work?

14:35.433 --> 14:38.784
You help us out
with the sting.

14:38.937 --> 14:41.437
We get Hayak, your gun buyer,

14:41.456 --> 14:43.256
and everything seized
in the raid.

14:44.943 --> 14:47.793
You...get to walk away

14:47.946 --> 14:49.596
a free man.

14:56.563 --> 15:00.732
No wires, no recording devices,
not on me.

15:02.218 --> 15:04.127
When all this is over,
Thony gets to walk too.

15:04.129 --> 15:07.155
No more working
as an informant.

15:11.319 --> 15:13.745
Sounds like a win-win-win
to me.

15:13.896 --> 15:16.806
<i> (edgy music)</i>

15:16.824 --> 15:18.625
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

15:26.409 --> 15:29.152
FIONA:
This is seriously sketchy.

15:29.154 --> 15:30.336
SAMENTHA:
All right.

15:30.413 --> 15:31.930
-Thanks, Vinny.
-VINNY: Yep.

15:32.081 --> 15:32.838
SAMENTHA:
Hope you get what you need.

15:32.991 --> 15:34.006
THONY:
Thanks, Sam.

15:34.083 --> 15:37.160
So, you're looking
for an antiviral, right?

15:37.162 --> 15:39.162
-Mm-hmm.
-I got acyclovir.

15:39.164 --> 15:42.589
And also
the immunosuppressant.

15:42.609 --> 15:44.000
Yeah, I got it.

15:44.002 --> 15:48.262
But...
this took some legwork.

15:48.281 --> 15:51.407
I'm gonna have to charge you
double what I told Samentha.

16:02.036 --> 16:04.128
It's fine.

16:04.280 --> 16:06.714
I'll take
everything you've got.

16:08.359 --> 16:10.760
Also got new batch
of antipsychotics.

16:12.213 --> 16:14.222
Why you looking at me?

16:17.702 --> 16:20.144
You really think I haven't
thought this through, Nadia?

16:20.221 --> 16:23.039
How would I know?
You didn't discuss it with me.

16:23.057 --> 16:24.131
Instead you decided to talk

16:24.209 --> 16:25.316
about our future
with the cleaning lady.

16:25.426 --> 16:27.301
She's giving us a way
through this.

16:27.320 --> 16:28.987
It's the only way we can get
our hands on those guns

16:29.063 --> 16:30.213
and close this deal with Noah.

16:30.231 --> 16:32.715
There are other ways.
(speaking Spanish)

16:32.734 --> 16:35.009
But you chose the way that's
gonna get us both killed.

16:35.086 --> 16:36.068
If not by Hayak,

16:36.221 --> 16:37.311
then anyone else
who finds out you're a rat.

16:37.330 --> 16:38.888
Nobody's gonna put
that together, Nadia.

16:38.890 --> 16:39.998
I'll make sure of that.

16:40.149 --> 16:41.741
You promised me you'd
cut her out of our lives.

16:41.817 --> 16:42.816
Not now, Nadia.

16:42.836 --> 16:45.294
(jazzy music playing)

16:46.673 --> 16:48.581
-Noah.
-Arman.

16:48.733 --> 16:50.258
So good to see you.

16:52.070 --> 16:54.679
Wow. You clean up well.

16:54.830 --> 16:56.973
Nadia. Always a pleasure.

16:59.394 --> 17:01.077
ARMAN:
So Noah,

17:01.095 --> 17:04.505
I want to apologize
for the delay.

17:04.524 --> 17:07.583
It's not the way
I like to do business.

17:07.585 --> 17:10.862
And we're all set
to deliver the inventory now.

17:11.013 --> 17:12.697
But there's a sticking point.

17:12.848 --> 17:15.682
I have a boss and my boss wants
to control the transaction.

17:15.760 --> 17:17.610
He wants to be sure
we're at a secure location.

17:17.762 --> 17:19.686
Arman, I get it.

17:19.764 --> 17:20.946
You can't be too careful.

17:21.023 --> 17:22.707
But, see, my sticking point
is that

17:22.784 --> 17:27.453
things are starting to feel
a little too...unpredictable.

17:27.530 --> 17:30.531
Missing deadlines,
radio silence.

17:30.550 --> 17:32.884
-Yeah.
-NOAH: Makes me uncomfortable.

17:33.035 --> 17:34.126
Well, you're right, you know.

17:34.203 --> 17:36.370
I haven't been
completely honest with you.

17:36.389 --> 17:39.115
I promised more
than I could deliver.

17:39.133 --> 17:40.374
Look,
we've been suffering the same

17:40.393 --> 17:42.301
post-pandemic
supply line shortages--

17:42.378 --> 17:44.896
Babe.
This isn't about the details.

17:45.047 --> 17:46.806
This is about trust.

17:46.958 --> 17:48.066
I understand how you feel.

17:48.217 --> 17:51.444
It's--it's hard to trust
after you've been lied to.

17:52.980 --> 17:56.074
Noah,
please accept our apology,

17:56.225 --> 18:00.745
and know that Arman
is a man of his word.

18:00.822 --> 18:02.988
We have the full shipment now.

18:03.141 --> 18:05.583
(soft dinner music plays)

18:05.660 --> 18:07.752
(background chatter)

18:13.334 --> 18:15.576
Okay.

18:15.595 --> 18:17.095
All right.

18:17.288 --> 18:21.265
But for my time and delay...

18:22.009 --> 18:24.102
I want a better deal.

18:24.253 --> 18:26.938
I'll tell you what,
you throw in a case

18:27.089 --> 18:29.682
of your carbon-neutral bourbon,

18:29.758 --> 18:31.016
I'll take off 5%.

18:31.093 --> 18:32.985
You got it.

18:41.195 --> 18:43.696
Where the hell
did you get these?

18:43.772 --> 18:45.289
Vincent? Fred?

18:45.366 --> 18:47.350
You don't even know
what's really in these bottles.

18:47.368 --> 18:50.628
All the pills are stamped.
You can see that.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.948
CHRIS:
(making animal noises)

18:54.968 --> 18:59.262
All right peanut, here you go.

19:01.457 --> 19:03.624
-Mmm--
-What?

19:03.643 --> 19:04.809
It's yucky.

19:04.960 --> 19:06.035
(sighs)

19:06.053 --> 19:08.053
They didn't have syrup
this time.

19:08.130 --> 19:10.314
Try again, okay?

19:11.484 --> 19:13.133
Come on.
You gotta drink it, buddy.

19:13.153 --> 19:15.319
You don't want
to get sick again, do you?

19:15.396 --> 19:16.712
No.

19:16.731 --> 19:18.305
CHRIS:
All right.

19:18.324 --> 19:19.806
Okay.
I'll put more juice in it.

19:19.884 --> 19:21.066
I'll be right back.

19:21.143 --> 19:22.551
Picky monster.

19:22.570 --> 19:25.371
(making playful noises)

19:27.225 --> 19:29.074
This is crazy.
You know that, right?

19:29.151 --> 19:30.910
We need to go home.

19:31.062 --> 19:32.003
(sighs)

19:32.154 --> 19:33.729
What about Fiona?

19:33.731 --> 19:35.173
Chris, Jaz?

19:35.249 --> 19:37.425
They're our home too.

19:38.994 --> 19:41.404
And you've seen
how happy he is.

19:41.422 --> 19:44.182
You really wanna take him
away from his family here?

19:44.184 --> 19:45.090
So you're saying
you want to stay.

19:45.243 --> 19:47.393
You've decided that now.

19:49.247 --> 19:52.598
THONY: I'm saying we need
to talk about it.

19:52.750 --> 19:54.233
That's all.

19:55.028 --> 19:58.103
(phone buzzing)

19:58.198 --> 20:00.740
Let me guess, that's him?

20:02.685 --> 20:03.868
(scoffs)

20:04.019 --> 20:05.352
You sure
he's not the real reason

20:05.430 --> 20:07.622
you want to stay in Vegas?

20:17.199 --> 20:20.033
Make sure Luca drinks this.

20:20.053 --> 20:22.628
And please don't put
any thoughts in his head

20:22.705 --> 20:24.538
about leaving.

20:24.615 --> 20:28.017
We need to decide this
together.

20:36.143 --> 20:38.552
(background chatter)

20:38.629 --> 20:41.647
(mellow pop music)

20:41.799 --> 20:43.557
♪ ♪

20:43.576 --> 20:45.493
-ARMAN: Hey.
-Hi.

20:46.637 --> 20:47.987
Thanks for meeting me here,
Isabel.

20:48.081 --> 20:51.474
Yeah, of course.
What's going on?

20:51.492 --> 20:53.918
So I looked into
the paperwork for you

20:53.995 --> 20:57.646
And your name's still tied to
all your father's businesses,

20:57.665 --> 20:59.315
including the trucking company.

20:59.317 --> 21:00.574
Did you speak with him?

21:00.593 --> 21:02.868
He told me his lawyers
were working on it.

21:03.020 --> 21:04.411
Yeah, well, they're not.

21:04.489 --> 21:07.598
So he's still lying to me then.

21:07.750 --> 21:10.326
I'm sure your father just wants
to provide for you.

21:10.344 --> 21:12.011
But if the FBI ever caught up
with him,

21:12.163 --> 21:14.272
you'd be implicated too,
Isabel.

21:15.942 --> 21:19.277
Okay.
So what is it, Arman?

21:19.428 --> 21:21.696
I mean, what does he ship
out of those trucks?

21:23.024 --> 21:24.532
Guns.

21:25.934 --> 21:27.526
Your father's
an illegal arms dealer.

21:27.678 --> 21:31.789
He ships them across the US,
Mexico, Armenia.

21:31.866 --> 21:34.000
It's an international
operation.

21:35.795 --> 21:37.778
(whispers) Oh, God.

21:37.872 --> 21:39.338
For how long?

21:40.449 --> 21:43.375
Since before I started
working for him.

21:43.452 --> 21:45.361
And my name is attached
to all of it?

21:45.379 --> 21:46.804
Maybe it won't be a problem.

21:46.806 --> 21:49.790
I just wanted to let you know,
because I care about you.

21:49.867 --> 21:51.958
And I don't want you to go down
for your father's crimes.

21:51.978 --> 21:55.646
No, I--I can't let that happen.

21:57.391 --> 22:00.526
I know of a way
you can protect yourself.

22:04.899 --> 22:06.198
RUSSO:
Hey.

22:11.906 --> 22:13.980
You hear from Thony yet?

22:14.000 --> 22:15.224
GARRETT:
Nope.

22:15.226 --> 22:18.336
And she's ignoring my calls.

22:20.565 --> 22:23.507
You really think Morales
is gonna deliver Barsamian?

22:25.994 --> 22:28.161
If he doesn't,

22:28.239 --> 22:29.972
you still firing me?

22:32.334 --> 22:35.001
I can probably dump you
on surveillance

22:35.079 --> 22:37.229
with the rest
of the broken wings.

22:39.341 --> 22:42.526
Yeah.
I'd rather be fired.

22:44.364 --> 22:47.681
What do you want from me,
Miller?

22:47.758 --> 22:50.259
My sympathy?

22:50.277 --> 22:52.778
Oh, I'd settle for friendship.

22:52.930 --> 22:55.614
That's manipulative.

22:55.766 --> 22:57.416
And you know it.

22:59.379 --> 23:01.194
We are friends,

23:01.196 --> 23:04.607
and you took advantage of that,

23:04.625 --> 23:06.675
of me.

23:08.963 --> 23:10.596
I--

23:14.376 --> 23:17.136
(mellow music playing)

23:17.230 --> 23:20.523
(indistinct chatter)

23:30.985 --> 23:32.076
Garrett's been calling me.

23:32.153 --> 23:34.286
I'm sure he wants to know
what the plan is.

23:34.396 --> 23:37.915
I'll let you know when and
where the deal's going down.

23:38.066 --> 23:40.492
But you should also know,

23:40.569 --> 23:44.313
I'm not letting the FBI
take everything from me.

23:44.315 --> 23:48.074
If you go back on the deal,
we'll both be arrested.

23:48.076 --> 23:49.760
Worse--you could be killed.

23:49.912 --> 23:52.988
That's true whether I do
what they want me to do or not.

23:52.990 --> 23:54.873
So I came up with my own plan.

23:54.951 --> 23:56.659
That's not what you agreed to.

23:56.661 --> 23:59.419
I'm not gonna trust the FBI
to do what they promise.

23:59.497 --> 24:02.181
I've seen it happen
too many times.

24:02.333 --> 24:04.183
So what are you gonna do?

24:04.335 --> 24:07.594
I'm gonna use that
to my advantage.

24:07.613 --> 24:09.572
Arman--

24:11.951 --> 24:15.494
You asked me once
if I trust you.

24:16.530 --> 24:20.332
I'm asking you now,
do you trust me?

24:25.690 --> 24:27.339
I do.

24:52.992 --> 24:55.993
(indistinct chatter)

24:58.647 --> 25:01.499
(chatter continues)

25:02.818 --> 25:06.086
(engine revving)

25:13.662 --> 25:16.572
<i> (tense music)</i>

25:16.590 --> 25:19.683
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:19.802 --> 25:21.260
(line ringing)

25:21.336 --> 25:24.263
Hey, how's the weather
down there?

25:24.415 --> 25:26.915
<i> RENEE: Can't complain.</i>
<i> Sun's shining.</i>

25:26.934 --> 25:28.934
<i> Looks like a good day</i>
<i> for a bust.</i>

25:29.086 --> 25:30.194
Yeah, well,
if you could see the digs

25:30.345 --> 25:33.255
that I'm kicking back in,
you might complain.

25:33.257 --> 25:35.257
We're all set to go
in the suite next door.

25:35.276 --> 25:38.351
Just waiting for the party
to start.

25:38.371 --> 25:40.538
Let me know
when you're ready to roll.

25:42.542 --> 25:43.782
-Anything?
-Nope.

25:43.934 --> 25:46.085
Still crickets over here.

25:47.605 --> 25:49.288
Oh--

25:49.364 --> 25:51.456
Hold on.

25:51.551 --> 25:53.384
Here we go.

25:55.203 --> 25:56.870
RUSSO:
There they are.

25:56.947 --> 25:58.204
And that's got
to be the cash, right?

25:58.299 --> 26:01.725
Yep. Looks like our boy's
playing ball after all.

26:01.727 --> 26:04.103
We'll see.

26:08.934 --> 26:10.067
Oh, I forgot to mention,

26:10.218 --> 26:13.979
a suite opened up
on the 38th floor.

26:14.131 --> 26:17.449
The view is much better
from the top.

26:21.655 --> 26:24.489
<i> (tense music)</i>

26:24.642 --> 26:31.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:56.098 --> 26:59.191
Something's not right.
Pull up the other hotel cams.

26:59.343 --> 27:02.328
Suite level hallways first,
37, 38.

27:04.457 --> 27:07.440
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

27:07.460 --> 27:14.131
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:27.204 --> 27:30.064
Make yourself at home.

27:33.093 --> 27:34.209
RUSSO:
There they are.

27:34.228 --> 27:36.228
Son of a bitch.
They changed suites.

27:36.304 --> 27:38.046
All right.
Take it easy, Miller.

27:38.065 --> 27:40.199
We may have lost visual,
but they're still here.

27:48.668 --> 27:50.817
That's the 38th floor.

27:50.836 --> 27:53.061
GARRETT:
What's the room number?

27:53.063 --> 27:55.839
-What's the room number?
-It's 3808.

27:55.841 --> 27:57.157
Okay, Let's go.

27:57.176 --> 28:00.585
Bourbon. This is how
you spend your billions?

28:00.738 --> 28:02.738
Look, if we don't reduce
the carbon footprint,

28:02.756 --> 28:04.239
we're not gonna have a future.

28:04.332 --> 28:06.241
Armenian children
are starving.

28:06.243 --> 28:08.593
People are dying
on war-torn streets.

28:08.595 --> 28:10.579
What about their future?
Huh?

28:10.581 --> 28:12.856
What matters
is we take care of everyone

28:13.083 --> 28:14.507
in whichever way we can.

28:14.527 --> 28:15.508
Yeah.

28:15.528 --> 28:18.487
(phone buzzing)

28:20.056 --> 28:22.366
Travis, talk to me, brother.

28:23.869 --> 28:25.594
We're all set.

28:25.596 --> 28:28.205
Locked and loaded.
Moving out now.

28:28.282 --> 28:30.040
MAN: All right,
let's go, let's go!

28:30.192 --> 28:31.858
They're headed out.
It's going down.

28:31.877 --> 28:33.877
All right, copy.

28:33.879 --> 28:35.620
Let's roll out.

28:35.697 --> 28:37.548
AGENT: Let's go.

28:42.296 --> 28:44.037
That's right.
Hayak's son is fighting

28:44.131 --> 28:46.281
for his homeland in Azerbaijan.

28:46.300 --> 28:49.727
Well, it's, uh,
certainly a noble cause.

28:49.878 --> 28:52.062
To saving the world.

28:53.715 --> 28:56.400
<i> (suspenseful music)</i>

28:56.477 --> 29:03.073
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:08.414 --> 29:11.331
(sirens wailing)

29:15.921 --> 29:18.163
AGENT: (over loudspeaker)
This is the FBI.

29:18.315 --> 29:20.090
(indistinct shouting
continues)

29:20.242 --> 29:24.219
TRAVIS: Turn around.
Now. Go! Go! Go!

29:27.157 --> 29:29.600
It's a bust!
We've been set up!

29:30.102 --> 29:33.061
-This is the FBI!
-(helicopter blades thrumming)

29:33.922 --> 29:35.664
(gunfire)

29:35.682 --> 29:37.274
(gunfire over phone)

29:38.335 --> 29:39.526
-(Arman grunts)
-(gunshot)

29:44.675 --> 29:46.325
(wincing and groaning)

29:48.345 --> 29:49.177
ALL:
FBI!

29:49.179 --> 29:51.847
RUSSO:
Hands up! Hands up!

29:51.865 --> 29:54.032
GARRETT:
Put the guns on the ground!

29:54.184 --> 29:58.128
-RUSSO: Hands up, hands up!
-GARRETT: On the ground!

30:00.282 --> 30:02.633
AGENT: Hands up.
You got any weapons on you?

30:02.784 --> 30:05.544
Hands up!

30:05.696 --> 30:08.472
<i> (uneasy music)</i>

30:08.623 --> 30:11.308
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:11.459 --> 30:12.518
(groans)

30:14.480 --> 30:16.555
You saved my life.

30:16.631 --> 30:18.232
GARRETT:
Take them away.

30:19.726 --> 30:20.984
All of them.

30:21.061 --> 30:24.321
(police radio chatter)

30:27.642 --> 30:30.369
(police radio chatter)

30:35.576 --> 30:37.726
Take it easy, man.

30:37.744 --> 30:38.818
Hey, I said take it easy.

30:38.838 --> 30:40.254
AGENT: Come on.
Let's go!

30:49.181 --> 30:50.755
All right, baby.
Show me the money.

30:50.908 --> 30:53.408
Huh?

30:53.427 --> 30:55.227
(grunts)

31:05.606 --> 31:07.513
Search the room.

31:07.533 --> 31:08.773
The money's not here.

31:08.926 --> 31:11.610
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

31:11.762 --> 31:16.689
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:16.767 --> 31:19.284
Stop all the housekeeping staff
from leaving the building.

31:19.361 --> 31:20.294
Now!

31:28.962 --> 31:30.554
Check all their carts.

31:30.705 --> 31:32.614
AGENT: Yes, sir.

31:32.633 --> 31:35.541
<i> (twangy music)</i>

31:35.561 --> 31:42.316
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:43.885 --> 31:48.322
<i> SINGER: ♪ You keep saying</i>
<i> you've got something for me ♪</i>

31:49.800 --> 31:53.535
<i> ♪ Something you call love,</i>
<i> but confess ♪</i>

31:55.563 --> 31:58.640
<i> ♪ You've been a-messin'</i>
<i> where you shouldn't have...♪</i>

31:58.659 --> 31:59.750
THONY:
Did you get it?

31:59.752 --> 32:01.810
You mean this?
(laughing)

32:01.812 --> 32:04.813
How can $6 million fit
in that tiny little thing?

32:04.815 --> 32:07.441
Cryptocurrency.

32:07.443 --> 32:10.410
Jackpot!

32:10.429 --> 32:13.079
<i> SINGER: ♪ That's just</i>
<i> what they'll do ♪</i>

32:13.098 --> 32:15.915
<i> ♪ One of these days</i>
<i> these boots are gonna ♪</i>

32:15.935 --> 32:17.434
<i> ♪ Walk all over you ♪</i>

32:21.832 --> 32:24.666
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

32:24.685 --> 32:25.943
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:26.094 --> 32:27.352
(knocking on door)

32:27.504 --> 32:29.321
Go away.

32:37.122 --> 32:39.456
You took that
from evidence?

32:39.533 --> 32:41.683
Just one bottle.

32:41.702 --> 32:44.686
No one's gonna miss it.

32:44.688 --> 32:46.612
Come on.

32:46.632 --> 32:49.257
It's billionaire's bourbon.

32:51.378 --> 32:53.220
(sighs)

33:03.707 --> 33:05.707
Just take the win, Miller.

33:05.800 --> 33:07.567
We got the bad guys.

33:08.988 --> 33:11.213
But with no money and no tape,

33:11.215 --> 33:13.973
they won't be locked up
for long.

33:13.993 --> 33:16.384
You won't be locked up,

33:16.403 --> 33:18.495
nor will Thony.

33:18.646 --> 33:21.906
You should be grateful
you got out of that one.

33:22.059 --> 33:24.543
Does that mean
I still have a job?

33:25.929 --> 33:27.912
Eh.

33:28.065 --> 33:31.008
It's more fun
having you around.

33:34.571 --> 33:37.180
(laughs)

33:45.766 --> 33:49.342
I'd say that's overrated.

33:49.419 --> 33:50.585
You would.

33:50.604 --> 33:52.437
(both chuckle)

33:52.514 --> 33:54.923
-(knocking on door)
-PERSON: Special Agent Miller,

33:54.925 --> 33:56.591
there's someone here
to see you.

33:56.610 --> 33:57.850
Thank you.

33:57.928 --> 34:00.779
<i> (tense music)</i>

34:00.931 --> 34:03.373
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:03.525 --> 34:06.692
I'm Isabel Barsamian,
Hayak's daughter.

34:06.770 --> 34:09.104
Look, I need you to know
that I have nothing to do

34:09.106 --> 34:10.881
with my father's businesses.

34:11.032 --> 34:13.717
I can go ahead
and hand over all his books

34:13.868 --> 34:15.443
and all his tax records.

34:15.445 --> 34:20.557
But only if you promise
to protect me and my husband.

34:30.627 --> 34:34.404
Noah must have been a rat.
I vetted him.

34:34.481 --> 34:36.055
Thought he was clear.
I apologize.

34:36.075 --> 34:38.316
He wasn't the only one.

34:38.393 --> 34:41.495
My own daughter handed
all my books to the Feds.

34:42.973 --> 34:45.582
Well, it was never
her world, Hayak.

34:45.659 --> 34:47.918
You were right, Arman.

34:47.994 --> 34:50.645
It's all a mess now.

34:50.647 --> 34:52.589
They searched the house.

34:52.740 --> 34:55.074
They found Tarik's gun.

34:55.094 --> 34:57.986
Now my idiot son
is wanted for murder.

34:57.988 --> 35:01.515
Thank God he is in Azerbaijan.

35:02.935 --> 35:05.827
Well,
you know I got your back,

35:05.829 --> 35:08.330
even on the inside.

35:08.348 --> 35:10.181
No.

35:10.334 --> 35:14.352
What I need is you
on the outside.

35:14.504 --> 35:19.765
My attorney thinks
he can get you released.

35:19.843 --> 35:21.767
I need you
to keep things going,

35:21.787 --> 35:25.363
the club, the trucks,

35:25.440 --> 35:26.848
everything.

35:26.867 --> 35:29.292
Course, Hayak.
Whatever you need.

35:29.444 --> 35:32.945
Get this in your head
for the accounts.

35:33.023 --> 35:35.373
But if you betray me again,

35:35.450 --> 35:39.711
there's no wall that could
stop me from finding you.

35:39.787 --> 35:42.697
Is that clear?

35:42.716 --> 35:45.700
You got it.

35:45.793 --> 35:49.795
<i> (tense music)</i>

35:49.815 --> 35:56.044
Three two three two...

35:56.046 --> 36:02.993
six eight four five.

36:05.906 --> 36:08.573
(buzzer blares)

36:08.650 --> 36:11.576
(indistinct chatter)

36:11.728 --> 36:13.461
ARMAN:
Thank you.

36:15.565 --> 36:16.590
Hey.

36:18.402 --> 36:19.426
Hey.

36:20.995 --> 36:23.430
How are you doing in here?

36:26.351 --> 36:30.187
It's a small price
for a big reward.

36:32.082 --> 36:33.915
Did you get
what you wanted then?

36:33.934 --> 36:36.026
Yeah.

36:41.015 --> 36:43.925
So what are you gonna
do now?

36:44.018 --> 36:48.413
You're staying here or are you
going back to the Philippines?

36:51.877 --> 36:55.528
Well, with you in here,

36:55.605 --> 36:59.474
it looks like
I'm gonna have to stay.

36:59.476 --> 37:02.444
<i> (tender music)</i>

37:02.462 --> 37:09.059
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:18.645 --> 37:21.613
GUARD: Hey.

37:22.799 --> 37:24.157
Yeah.

37:29.731 --> 37:34.918
Well, you won't regret
making your home here.

37:35.069 --> 37:39.756
After all, America
is a land of opportunity.

37:39.907 --> 37:45.220
All you need is the right
combination to unlock it.

37:48.158 --> 37:52.343
<i> (quiet music)</i>

37:52.496 --> 37:58.591
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:58.668 --> 38:02.020
<i> SINGER: ♪ Bite my tongue,</i>
<i> bide my time ♪</i>

38:02.096 --> 38:05.189
<i> ♪ Wearing a warning sign ♪</i>

38:05.266 --> 38:08.493
<i> ♪ Wait till the world</i>
<i> is mine ♪</i>

38:11.698 --> 38:14.808
<i> ♪ Visions I vandalize ♪</i>

38:14.810 --> 38:17.943
